when the receiver thread fails to retrieve the message withing 5 seconds timeout. 

So first thing I would check is your [MQ broker container logs][1] 

In general [JMeter in non-GUI mode has much better performance than in GUI mode][2] so it might be the case it just overloads your MQ broker instance and it cannot properly respond on message receive requests. 

Apart from checking the logs you can additionally ensure that the broker has enough headroom to operate in terms of CPU, RAM, Network, Disk, etc. It can be done using container monitoring solution like [docker stats][3] or [JMeter PerfMon Plugin][4]. If this is the case you might need to increase [container limits][5] or [Docker engine][6]  


